Ramp Rate:
\i0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 When turning off a Hue Bulb, Ramp Rates higher than 60 seconds result in the bulb fading at the expected rate but suddenly turning off about 60 seconds after the fade-out begins. This appears to be a bug in how the Hue hub handles slow transitions to "off" with Hue bulbs. This does not appear to affect LightStrips or LivingColors devices. Currently, the only workaround is to set the brightness to 1 percent using the desired Ramp Rate, then create a second action in Indigo to turn off the Hue Bulb that's delayed by the same amount of time as the Ramp Rate.\
