RGB States:
\i0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 Because Philips Hue devices (especially the bulbs) are not true RGB light emitters (i.e. they don't have a true red, green, and blue LED), it's not possible for them to output every color represented by the RGB values that can be specified. Thus, while you can tell a Hue Bulb to display a RGB color of 0 red, 255 green, and 255 blue, the Hue Bulb will only show the closest color it can display to the requested color.\
